      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/653057195_18568128229015522_2693241671525923325_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=107&amp;ig_cache_key=MTY0ODA5OTI1NjQwNDc5ODMyNg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTA4MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=mdUpvBOvhIgQ7kNvwG0ZxZT&amp;_nc_oc=AdoWspFMG0uqYU6FYzUFli7Chik1jD8SgbSGmJZlZbJh1iSeYJUK2PIY2bUFEMf2I1E&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=nJb-xcF_CrLXsikWh1lnFA&amp;_nc_ss=7a3ba&amp;oh=00_Af3dlGdKn74828gQG3uJarF8ZJTHp18GBbKKPqx7tX4lDQ&amp;oe=69D36597" alt="Slide 1 fra @jmbjmbjmbjmbjmbjmb" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/652216458_18566878387034616_8145891906019980188_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=108&amp;ig_cache_key=MTY0ODA5OTI1NjIzNjg3OTYwMg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjgzOHg4Mzguc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=3QMQM5-LA8sQ7kNvwGgVxlb&amp;_nc_oc=Adqu_xlBRdI3roYuILlhsQuertF1f7gfeB5K0bWnmmG8yLTMBsFA4MEV0sWN0vM_S90&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=8&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=nJb-xcF_CrLXsikWh1lnFA&amp;_nc_ss=7a3ba&amp;oh=00_Af1vyrOvYqK57en5lZJjtMgPQP6gZuLLnPIXbcuKUhT1GQ&amp;oe=69D37E4F" alt="Slide 2 fra @jmbjmbjmbjmbjmbjmb" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/652131502_18397960000145980_840683174824344118_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=108&amp;ig_cache_key=MTY0ODA5OTI2MzYxODg0MzQ5OA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjc3OHg3Nzguc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=8eD9F_g8EHsQ7kNvwFszON4&amp;_nc_oc=AdqIUcoVLONupgmqIDOECPiLvk416Ui5JZ6dCG1wrTq8cGVhBbT76qS_gdfouGbNe8A&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=nJb-xcF_CrLXsikWh1lnFA&amp;_nc_ss=7a3ba&amp;oh=00_Af2ydaozW9kKmpq1gdMhCKl96qd9nRuwmfWkRiUOiBBQUQ&amp;oe=69D35034" alt="Slide 3 fra @jmbjmbjmbjmbjmbjmb" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/649530278_18446656372106459_57727103212115432_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=109&amp;ig_cache_key=MTY0ODA5OTI2NDQ3NDU1MDEyNA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjY0MHg2NDAuc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=itYX_v4C3xAQ7kNvwFY2vRc&amp;_nc_oc=Adqo-rTzg_oPSl2vUdKg1b0jtb2Br9VPRv2NtnwPUjGyb7AI7PW920-Cvx0lVFEYXrE&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=nJb-xcF_CrLXsikWh1lnFA&amp;_nc_ss=7a3ba&amp;oh=00_Af3cEsTxA6-_zvcXCQ-O3rnxLM6vemfokMElhM0V1610Kg&amp;oe=69D354A4" alt="Slide 4 fra @jmbjmbjmbjmbjmbjmb" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /></p><p><strong>🖼️ Slideshow (7 medier)</strong></p><p><strong>@jmbjmbjmbjmbjmbjmb</strong></p><p>Ash was my friend. Ash was special. Ash would drop by the culturesport studio frequently - almost always unanounced - being heads down in my own world most of the time It would often bug the shit out of me but thats on me because by the time he left having dropped off a book for reference or playing a game of chess with Greg or helping me figure a way out of a creative block i would be pissed that he wasnt still there. Ash believed in what i do more than i did when i needed it the most. Ash believed in what i do more than i did when i didnt need it at all. Ash was the only person i could talk to about the fantasatic four in a genuine-12-year-old-kind-of-a-way. Ash was constantly amazed that Desi would even bother hanging around him let alone partner with him. Ash was enthralled with Desi. Ash spoke so often about how much strength he drew from her - Ash never said it quite as hallmarky as that though. Ash knew how lucky he was to have her. Ash was his own soul. I think Ash was his own soul for the singular purpose of being everyone eleses constant soul support. Ash was not selfish in any way that actually matters. Ash would always be brutally honest with me ALWAYS ALWAYS ALWAYS but ALWAYS in the sweetest and most thoughtful way i cant even begin to describe. ( it was really supernatural ). from the moment i met Ash we were second nature to each other in a way he realized earlier than I did. Ash started alot of his sentences to me with a quasi-inqusitive inflection of the word “Man..” i can remember his inflection with crystal-clear-cold-clarity. Ash was wild. Ash was like wild wild. Ash was wild like a son i would worry about but 30 years later i would realize that i  shouldnt have because he knew himself better than i ever could know my ownself. Ash was wild and so sweet in a way that ive never seen another human be - like one of the illustrations of the wild things in where the wild things are like-seriously-in-the-most-sincere-least-twee-but-twees-aight-if-thats-your-thing-but im-real-which-means-wild-in-an-organic-way-that-transcends-your-capability-to-be-real-but-im-not-aware-of-it-because-im-so-real-but-dont-ever-obsess-over-my-own-realness-kind-of-a-way.</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/BbfOmPrFts-/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></description>
